The paper deals with decision fusion in multi-sensor networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The presence of byzantine nodes also makes it relevant to the field of security and privacy (cs.CR). The proposed algorithm is based on message passing, which is a common technique in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also considers the case of Markovian system states, which falls under the category of control and optimization (cs.SY).
